"closed_at": null, "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "If you have files with a newline of '\\r', the only way to handle them is to use split. But if you have files with a newline of '\\n' or '\\r\\n', then you can use lines().\r\n\r\nThis is counterintuitive and problematic from the perspective of the BufRead interface - there's no way to use it to iterate over any of the three types. I'd typically expect that lines() would handle this transparently.\r\n\r\nI'm not sure if this is the right place, but I don't want it to get lost because it cost me major hassle.", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/55743/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/55743/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}